WhatsApp Channel Rules:
- Idempotency: Rails.cache key "twilio_msg:#{MessageSid}" 24h via Solid Cache
- Reply chunks: max 1550 chars, split_for_whatsapp, 0.5s gap between Twilio sends
- NO Markdown tables in WhatsApp output. Use ① ② ③, emojis, plain text
- Media flow: ProcessWhatsappMediaJob → compress (ruby-vips) → S3 upload (wa_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_N.ext) → KbSyncService → BedrockIngestionJob
- conv_session_id MUST be passed through entire job chain
- Locale: sticky per-thread via Rails.cache (7d TTL), short follow-ups (≤200 chars) inherit previous locale
- session_id is NOT forwarded to Bedrock for WhatsApp (stateless retrieval — intentional design choice)
- TwilioController responds with empty TwiML immediately; actual RAG runs in background job
- whatsapp_from = our Twilio number (to from webhook), whatsapp_to = end user (from from webhook)
